    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fairness in the Alito Hearings'' (editorial, Jan. 11):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Fairness in the Alito Hearings'' (editorial, Jan. 11):</p>
        <p>You say it's unfortunate that federal appeals court judges who know Judge Samuel A. Alito Jr. (who are not partisan liberals or conservatives) are coming to his defense.</p>
        <p>Your editorial page, which has clearly been against Judge Alito since he was nominated, is worried.</p>
        <p>You write: This is ''a move that could reasonably be construed as a partisan gesture. The judges will be doing harm to the federal bench.''</p>
        <p>The harm to the federal bench comes from senators and editorial boards demanding that prospective jurists pledge allegiance to or disdain for a single issue, Roe v. Wade.</p>
        <p>Matt Manochio  Succasunna, N.J., Jan. 11, 2006</p>
      </block>
